---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Giuseppe's Lair - About">
    <h1>About Giuseppe's Lair</h1>
    <p>
        Welcome to my personal blog, where I share my thoughts on mathematics,
        coding, and various other topics that fascinate me as a computer science
        student.
    </p>

    <div class="profile">
        <img
            src="/images/giuseppe-profile.jpg"
            alt="Giuseppe"
            class="profile-image"
        />
        <div class="profile-info">
            <h2>About Me</h2>
            <p>
                I'm Jos√© Pedro Barraza, a passionate computer science student at
                Pontificia Universidad Catolica de Chile with a love for
                mathematics and coding. Through this blog, I aim to:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Share insights on mathematical concepts and their
                    applications in computer science
                </li>
                <li>Discuss interesting coding projects and techniques</li>
                <li>
                    Explore the intersection of math, technology, and computer
                    science
                </li>
                <li>
                    Document my learning journey and personal growth in the
                    field
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>My Fascination with Fractals</h2>
    <p>
        One of my favorite subjects in computer science is the study of
        fractals. These complex, self-similar patterns showcase the beauty that
        can emerge from simple mathematical rules and iterative processes.
    </p>
    <img
        src="/images/complex-fractal.png"
        alt="Complex Antisymmetrical Fractal"
        class="fractal-image"
    />
    <p>
        This image represents a complex, antisymmetrical fractal that I find
        particularly intriguing. It demonstrates how seemingly chaotic patterns
        can arise from deterministic processes, a concept that I often explore
        in my studies and personal projects.
    </p>

    <div class="math-quote">
        <blockquote>
            "Mathematics is the language in which God has written the universe."
            - Galileo Galilei
        </blockquote>
    </div>
</Layout>

<style>
    h1,
    h2 {
        color: rgb(var(--accent));
    }
    .profile {
        display: flex;
        align-items: start;
        gap: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    .profile-image {
        width: 200px;
        height: auto;
        border-radius: 50%;
    }
    .profile-info {
        flex: 1;
    }
    ul {
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    .fractal-image {
        max-width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        border-radius: 8px;
        margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    .math-quote {
        background-color: rgba(var(--accent-light), 0.2);
        border-left: 4px solid rgb(var(--accent));
        padding: 1rem;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        font-style: italic;
    }
</style>
